  sodium: 1 g
  serving size: 603
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Halve the @red pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into very small pieces. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium high heat. Add the onion, pepper and carrot and cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(stalks and all). Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into small pieces) then zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{} and pop into a #mixing bowl{}. Use a #potato masher{} to roughly mash up about half of the chickpeas.

Once the veggies have softened, add the garlic, tomato, half the parsley, the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @tomato puree{30%ml} to the saucepan. Stir well and cook for ~{1%minute}, then tip in the chickpeas, @water{250%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1}. Stir to dissolve the stock powder, bring to the boil then simmer for ~{5%minutes}.

Place the @coley fillet{2} onto a #board{}. Sprinkle over half the remaining chopped parsley, all the lemon zest and a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a small drizzle of @?olive oil{} (optional but great for taste!) then use your hands to rub the flavourings all over the fish. Carefully lay the fillets on top of the stew.

Pop a #lid{} on the saucepan and continue to cook gently for ~{12-15%minutes} - you are steaming the fish!

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when flakey and opaque in the middle.

In the meantime, heat a small #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15} and toast until lightly golden, stirring occasionally, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them carefully, they can easily burn!

Once the fish is cooked, carefully place on a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Bring the stew to the boil and simmer for ~{2%minutes} to thicken the sauce. Stir the remaining parsley into the stew and season to taste with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if necessary. Spoon the stew into #bowls{} and carefully top with the fish. Finish with a squeeze of lemon juice and a sprinkling of almonds all over. Enjoy!